Oh and for all those having problems with blue screen. I too have this problem but all you have to do is go into manage apps or apps in your settings click on the game, tap force close ( you'll probably get a message saying are you sure it may cause the game to misbehave) but seen as its misbehaving anyway just go ahead and press yes. Then the next time you go on it, it will start up normally and from the place you were up to when you exited to main menu. Hope this helps :)

This is, in my opinion, an excellent game. The graphics are exceptional on my Bionic phone. The storyline is unique, and the controls are easy to use. I especially like the fact that you can zoom in and out of hidden object scenes. Overall, I highly recommend this game.  *EDIT* The spammy ads that someone mentioned are actually a request to rate the game and an offer for two free PC or MAC game downloads from BigFish Games. just click on them once, then either complete them or back out and you won't see them again. As for the two free games, I received Ravenhearst and Fairway Solitaire for PC. These games are normally offered on BFG's website for $9.99 for non-members and $6.99 for members. I don't think you have to join to get the free games.

Having played a few of their other games, I was disappointed with this one.  Not as many puzzles as many of their games though it was longer than some of the other of its genre.  It was extremely linear and the story was contrived enough to be annoying.  The hidden object could definitely use a zoom, considering they alternate between hidden in plain sight and translucent overlay within the same scene.  The puzzles, though few, were good and sometimes challenging.  It intrigued me enough to finished it, but just barely.  Thus the 3.  Still, going to try out the next one due to a review on here that says it's better.  I'll review it there.  Oh yeah, definitely NEED that game exit.  As with the others, I had to go to apps/force close to get back into the game.  Not good guys.  You should trust that when people leave the game, they'll want to be back.  It would be lovely if you fixed that.
